WEBVTT

00:04.170 --> 00:07.506
<i>Previously on</i>
Dexter: Original Sin...

00:07.507 --> 00:10.384
[Dexter] What if this victim
and the last two we found,

00:10.385 --> 00:13.053
<i>the one in Overtown and
the sex worker in Coconut Grove,</i>

00:13.054 --> 00:14.388
what if they're all connected?

00:14.389 --> 00:16.223
You're shitting me.
A serial killer?

00:16.224 --> 00:17.850
No one in shitting you, Captain.

00:17.851 --> 00:19.727
All the victims come
from high-risk population,

00:19.728 --> 00:20.853
all loners.

00:20.854 --> 00:21.895
Nothing was taken from them,

00:21.896 --> 00:23.230
so robbery isn't a motive.

00:23.231 --> 00:24.565
What do <i>you</i> think?

00:24.566 --> 00:26.025
I think she's on
to something, Aaron.

00:26.026 --> 00:27.359
<i>I think it's worth pursuing.</i>

00:27.360 --> 00:28.402
[Bean]
Someone took a fire poker,

00:28.403 --> 00:29.737
beat the guy like a piñata.

00:29.738 --> 00:31.238
Kept going
after the candy came out.

00:31.239 --> 00:33.741
- Any suspects?
- [Harry] <i>Moser?</i>

00:33.742 --> 00:35.743
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

00:35.744 --> 00:38.537
<i>♪</i>

00:38.538 --> 00:39.664
Holy shit.

00:40.415 --> 00:41.499
Fuck.

00:42.584 --> 00:45.753
I got the top score in <i>Dragon
Ninjas</i> at Pirates Arcade.

00:45.754 --> 00:47.714
- You can find me under "NAS."
- Cool.

00:48.256 --> 00:49.715
- [grunts]
- [Deb] <i>Got kicked</i>

00:49.716 --> 00:51.759
off the team
and suspended from school.

00:51.760 --> 00:53.093
What about the scholarship?

00:53.094 --> 00:54.511
There's a big shipment
of cocaine

00:54.512 --> 00:56.055
heading to New York
tomorrow night.

00:56.056 --> 00:57.182
This is it.

00:59.893 --> 01:00.934
Dex, what do you think

01:00.935 --> 01:02.062
- of Mommy's nails?
- Pretty.

01:03.104 --> 01:04.563
- Oh, my... No.
- [Dexter] No.

01:04.564 --> 01:06.690
- [Laura screaming]
- Come here.

01:06.691 --> 01:08.525
No!

01:08.526 --> 01:09.735
[Estrada]
Laura,

01:09.736 --> 01:11.195
I'm disappointed in you.

01:11.196 --> 01:13.113
Spare my boys.

01:13.114 --> 01:16.117
- [chain saw roaring]
- [man screaming]

01:18.161 --> 01:20.079
[Laura]
Please, don't, please.

01:20.080 --> 01:21.747
I know
this is gonna sound crazy,

01:21.748 --> 01:23.999
but I think Captain Spencer
killed Jimmy Powell

01:24.000 --> 01:25.292
and kidnapped Nicky.

01:25.293 --> 01:26.335
That <i>is</i> crazy.

01:26.336 --> 01:27.420
Dad?

01:30.131 --> 01:32.300
Nicky Spencer was spotted
at a known cartel stash house.

01:33.676 --> 01:34.802
Tell me where my fucking son is, motherfucker.

01:34.803 --> 01:36.595
- Aaron, stop.
- I'll blow

01:36.596 --> 01:38.347
- your fucking head off...
- [overlapping shouting]

01:38.348 --> 01:39.932
Gun!

01:39.933 --> 01:42.726
[screaming]

01:42.727 --> 01:43.977
- [automatic gunfire]
- Officer down!

01:43.978 --> 01:45.479
Oh, shit. [gasps]

01:45.480 --> 01:46.981
[Angel] Keep pressure,
just keep pressure.

01:51.528 --> 01:53.570
<i>♪ percussive music ♪</i>

01:53.571 --> 01:54.947
<i>♪</i>

01:54.948 --> 01:56.741
[mosquito buzzing]

02:00.078 --> 02:02.080
<i>♪</i>

02:31.025 --> 02:33.152
<i>♪</i>

02:33.153 --> 02:35.488
[knife sharpening]

03:02.056 --> 03:04.684
<i>♪</i>

03:19.407 --> 03:21.658
<i>♪ tranquil music ♪</i>

03:21.659 --> 03:23.703
<i>♪</i>

03:34.881 --> 03:38.384
I-29. I-29.

03:41.137 --> 03:43.723
[balls clattering]

03:45.308 --> 03:46.935
N-37.

03:47.936 --> 03:49.603
N-37.

03:49.604 --> 03:50.729
[sighs]

03:50.730 --> 03:52.773
Oh, you missed N-37 there.

03:52.774 --> 03:54.483
[Barb]
Oh.

03:54.484 --> 03:58.737
Well, who says the art
of being a gentleman is dead?

03:58.738 --> 04:00.530
[both laugh]

04:00.531 --> 04:04.243
What are you doing playing
bingo with all us crones?

04:04.244 --> 04:07.162
My mom always said,
"Bingo is the best way to gamble

04:07.163 --> 04:10.499
without losing all
of your money," so here I am.

04:10.500 --> 04:14.462
[laughing] Well, your mother
is a wise woman.

04:16.339 --> 04:17.297
I'm Barb.

04:17.298 --> 04:18.966
[balls clattering]

04:18.967 --> 04:20.759
Brian.

04:20.760 --> 04:23.971
[priest]
B-6. B-6.

04:23.972 --> 04:25.264
[laughing]
Oh, my God, oh.

04:25.265 --> 04:26.307
- Bingo!
- So soon.

04:27.809 --> 04:31.228
You are my lucky charm tonight.
Don't you go anywhere.

04:31.229 --> 04:33.273
- [Barb laughing]
- I wouldn't dream of it, Barb.

04:38.111 --> 04:40.070
<i>♪ ominous music ♪</i>

04:40.071 --> 04:42.615
<i>♪</i>

04:45.660 --> 04:46.786
Hey.

04:47.954 --> 04:50.205
Batista, how's he doing?
How's Bobby?

04:50.206 --> 04:51.540
Shot in the neck.

04:51.541 --> 04:53.000
Massive blood loss.
He's in surgery.

04:53.001 --> 04:54.042
- Jesus Christ.
- I'm so sorry.

04:54.043 --> 04:55.669
Yeah.

04:55.670 --> 04:57.129
Hey, well, what about his wife?
Does she know?

04:57.130 --> 04:58.463
Missy's in
the surgical waiting area,

04:58.464 --> 04:59.798
hoping on an update
from the surgeon.

04:59.799 --> 05:01.301
It's a nightmare.

05:04.887 --> 05:07.472
You mind if I have
a word with you?

05:07.473 --> 05:09.642
Sure.

05:11.144 --> 05:12.894
What?

05:12.895 --> 05:14.688
Look, I know
that it's a crazy time.

05:14.689 --> 05:15.856
[scoffs]

05:15.857 --> 05:17.566
But if we're gonna be partners,

05:17.567 --> 05:19.277
I need you
to come clean with me.

05:20.570 --> 05:21.654
What are you talking about?

05:22.655 --> 05:25.532
I saw you steal the file
from Tampa PD.

05:25.533 --> 05:26.700
[sighs]

05:26.701 --> 05:28.703
Who is Brian Moser?

05:32.540 --> 05:36.543
He's from a vice case
Bobby and I worked back in '73.

05:36.544 --> 05:39.880
We were trying to get
inside the Estrada Cartel.

05:39.881 --> 05:43.009
We had an informant,
a woman, Laura Moser.

05:44.177 --> 05:45.927
Mother of Brian.

05:45.928 --> 05:47.263
And?

05:49.390 --> 05:51.184
She was killed.

05:52.518 --> 05:53.894
It was my fault.

05:53.895 --> 05:55.520
Your fault how?

05:55.521 --> 05:57.940
[exhales]
I was having an affair with her.

05:59.442 --> 06:01.068
Emotions got in the way.

06:01.069 --> 06:02.652
[sighs]

06:02.653 --> 06:04.864
It's one of the biggest regrets
of my life.

06:06.032 --> 06:08.950
I always wondered
what happened to little Brian.

06:08.951 --> 06:11.704
[sighs]
Such a sweet kid.

06:13.790 --> 06:15.499
So that's why you stole
the file.

06:15.500 --> 06:17.542
This has nothing to do
with our case.

06:17.543 --> 06:20.045
All right?
This is a private matter,

06:20.046 --> 06:22.048
and I'd prefer
to keep it that way.

06:26.094 --> 06:27.220
[sighs]

06:28.262 --> 06:29.930
Bobby and I swung
by Laura's place.

06:29.931 --> 06:33.266
The house was torn apart,
there was food on the floor.

06:33.267 --> 06:34.893
Laura and her boys have
been kidnapped.

06:34.894 --> 06:37.270
I can feel it
in every fiber of my being.

06:37.271 --> 06:40.441
So you want me to jeopardize
the Estrada case on a feeling?

06:41.943 --> 06:44.277
The case. [chuckles]

06:44.278 --> 06:46.072
The case...

06:47.240 --> 06:49.241
The case is compromised.

06:49.242 --> 06:51.743
What the fuck
are you talking about?

06:51.744 --> 06:53.286
[sighs softly]

06:53.287 --> 06:55.789
I had an affair with Laura.

06:55.790 --> 06:58.167
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

06:59.168 --> 07:01.253
- I know.
- [Spencer sighs]

07:01.254 --> 07:02.879
I know, I fucked up.

07:02.880 --> 07:05.966
One of Estrada's henchmen
probably saw us together.

07:05.967 --> 07:07.885
Oh, Jesus, Harry.

07:09.095 --> 07:10.595
Does Doris know?

07:10.596 --> 07:12.097
That doesn't matter.

07:12.098 --> 07:15.267
You know what the cartel
will do to an informant.

07:15.268 --> 07:17.394
Spence, they have her two boys.

07:17.395 --> 07:19.187
- Any idea where they are?
- PortMiami docks.

07:19.188 --> 07:20.730
Estrada does
all of his business there.

07:20.731 --> 07:22.108
I can lead the charge.

07:23.818 --> 07:26.194
[scoffs, sighs]

07:26.195 --> 07:27.447
You can join the search.

07:29.240 --> 07:30.740
But as a uni.

07:30.741 --> 07:34.662
Give me your shield.
Give me your shield.

07:45.381 --> 07:46.965
[Spencer]
<i>We are looking for a mother</i>

07:46.966 --> 07:49.468
<i>and her two boys,
age seven and three.</i>

07:49.469 --> 07:52.345
<i>They could be in any shipping
container on the premises,</i>

07:52.346 --> 07:54.848
<i>but we cannot open any
without probable cause,</i>

07:54.849 --> 07:56.808
<i>so any proof of life</i>

07:56.809 --> 08:00.353
in a shipping container is
enough to crack open the lock,

08:00.354 --> 08:01.938
so if there is a whimper,
a scream,

08:01.939 --> 08:03.690
a K-9 indicating a scent,

08:03.691 --> 08:05.358
<i>that's good enough.</i>

08:05.359 --> 08:07.319
- You understand me?
- Yes, Captain, sir.

08:07.320 --> 08:08.528
All right, dismissed.
Let's get it done.

08:08.529 --> 08:09.779
[indistinct chatter]

08:09.780 --> 08:11.781
<i>♪ urgent music ♪</i>

08:11.782 --> 08:13.826
<i>♪</i>

08:25.296 --> 08:27.964
- [dog panting]
- [indistinct radio chatter]

08:27.965 --> 08:29.342
[knocking]

08:32.136 --> 08:34.180
[indistinct radio chatter]

08:38.518 --> 08:41.394
[knocking]

08:41.395 --> 08:43.688
No fucking way we're gonna
find them in all this.

08:43.689 --> 08:46.525
Hey, we're gonna find them.

08:46.526 --> 08:48.903
You keep looking. Go!

08:50.363 --> 08:52.406
Go on, keep looking!

08:55.117 --> 08:57.620
[knocking]

09:05.378 --> 09:07.213
Not gonna give up.

09:08.548 --> 09:10.383
Gonna find you.

09:19.141 --> 09:21.518
[speaking indistinctly]

09:21.519 --> 09:24.479
I can't even imagine what
he's going through right now.

09:24.480 --> 09:27.065
[Dexter]
<i>Spencer had everyone fooled,</i>

09:27.066 --> 09:28.692
<i>but not me.</i>

09:28.693 --> 09:31.987
<i>For him, pain was pleasure,</i>

09:31.988 --> 09:34.739
<i>the difference between the two
razor-thin.</i>

09:34.740 --> 09:37.784
<i>Spencer was my first
child killer,</i>

09:37.785 --> 09:39.661
<i>true evil incarnate.</i>

09:39.662 --> 09:41.246
[Spencer]
He's still alive, I know it.

09:41.247 --> 09:43.915
- You just have to find him.
- Yes.

09:43.916 --> 09:45.209
Find him.

09:47.503 --> 09:49.796
[sighs]

09:49.797 --> 09:52.425
We can't let Bobby's sacrifice
be in vain.

09:53.676 --> 09:55.468
He would want all of us
out there right now

09:55.469 --> 09:58.139
shaking the goddamn cartel tree
until we find my son.

09:59.307 --> 10:01.850
Our son.

10:01.851 --> 10:04.185
[Dexter] <i>In that moment,
I, too, had an intense need</i>

10:04.186 --> 10:06.314
<i>to find out
what had happened to Nicky.</i>

10:08.649 --> 10:11.193
<i>And there was only one person
who knew.</i>

10:13.195 --> 10:15.655
<i>♪ melancholy music ♪</i>

10:15.656 --> 10:17.657
<i>♪</i>

10:17.658 --> 10:19.952
[insects trilling]

10:21.037 --> 10:22.787
<i>♪ pulsing, exciting music ♪</i>

10:22.788 --> 10:25.665
[Dexter]
<i>Spencer's bachelor pad.</i>

10:25.666 --> 10:28.585
<i>For a minute I thought I'd
walked into the wrong apartment.</i>

10:28.586 --> 10:31.672
<i>The place didn't look like
the home of a police captain.</i>

10:32.715 --> 10:36.594
<i>But it did work as a crash pad
for a recently divorced husband.</i>

10:39.847 --> 10:41.306
<i>Children's charcuterie.</i>

10:41.307 --> 10:43.350
<i>What a concept.</i>

10:43.351 --> 10:44.643
[sets down box]

10:44.644 --> 10:46.771
<i>♪</i>

11:15.549 --> 11:18.134
<i>Shakespeare was right.</i>

11:18.135 --> 11:22.555
<i>You can smile and smile and all
the while still be a villain.</i>

11:22.556 --> 11:25.433
[keys jangling]

11:25.434 --> 11:28.312
[lock clicks]

11:29.522 --> 11:31.731
[door opens]

11:31.732 --> 11:34.694
[Spencer groans]
Thank you for the ride home.

11:35.653 --> 11:37.404
God, I've been up
for 20 hours straight.

11:37.405 --> 11:39.239
I'm bleary-eyed as hell.

11:39.240 --> 11:41.366
[exhales] Well, you have had
the shittiest of shitty days.

11:41.367 --> 11:44.703
[Dexter] <i>Sometimes I thought
Harry was a little too kind.</i>

11:44.704 --> 11:46.454
[Spencer groans softly]

11:46.455 --> 11:47.832
Yeah.

11:49.125 --> 11:52.043
I just still can't believe those
sons of bitches opened fire

11:52.044 --> 11:53.962
- on us.
- Hey,

11:53.963 --> 11:55.755
look, we found Nicky's jersey.

11:55.756 --> 11:57.924
Next, we're gonna find Nicky.

11:57.925 --> 11:59.926
Yeah. I need a drink.

11:59.927 --> 12:03.221
I got a bottle of Glenfiddich
around here somewhere.

12:03.222 --> 12:05.223
- [mutters]
- [Harry] I can't say no to that.

12:05.224 --> 12:06.434
[Spencer]
All right.

12:07.810 --> 12:09.562
[sighs]

12:11.313 --> 12:13.315
<i>♪ dramatic musical sting ♪</i>

12:19.280 --> 12:21.865
<i>♪ pulsing, exciting music ♪</i>

12:21.866 --> 12:24.243
<i>♪</i>

12:42.553 --> 12:44.929
<i>♪ whimsical music ♪</i>

12:44.930 --> 12:47.641
<i>♪</i>

12:49.143 --> 12:51.269
[sighs]

12:51.270 --> 12:52.395
Oh, hi.

12:52.396 --> 12:53.980
Uh, any news about Bobby?

12:53.981 --> 12:57.442
Uh, next 24 hours are critical.

12:57.443 --> 13:00.487
Hey, thanks for getting
your sister out of Bimini.

13:00.488 --> 13:01.988
Oh, not a problem.

13:01.989 --> 13:04.282
It was fun to be out
on Camilla's boat.

13:04.283 --> 13:06.242
Ah. [chuckles]

13:06.243 --> 13:08.621
<i>Slice of Pie.</i> So good.

13:10.289 --> 13:11.998
How goes your hunt
for our serial killer?

13:11.999 --> 13:14.543
<i>♪ dramatic musical sting ♪</i>

13:16.003 --> 13:18.171
Uh, the suspect
we thought was good for it,

13:18.172 --> 13:21.341
he was, uh,
killed a few weeks ago.

13:21.342 --> 13:23.259
Well, is it connected?

13:23.260 --> 13:25.512
Uh, you think the killer has
four homicides under his belt?

13:25.513 --> 13:26.679
[sighs]

13:26.680 --> 13:28.640
[slurps]

13:28.641 --> 13:31.142
Honestly, I don't think
any of 'em are related.

13:31.143 --> 13:32.645
It's not a serial killer case.

13:33.687 --> 13:35.271
[Dexter]
<i>I'll never forget the first time</i>

13:35.272 --> 13:37.482
<i>my father lied to my face.</i>

13:37.483 --> 13:38.567
Oh.

13:40.903 --> 13:43.196
Uh, hey, that was mine.

13:43.197 --> 13:44.823
[gulps]

13:44.824 --> 13:46.616
[Deb]
Before you say anything,

13:46.617 --> 13:47.659
I dumped Gio.

13:47.660 --> 13:49.577
It's <i>finito.</i>

13:49.578 --> 13:51.996
You can ground me for a month.
I know I deserve it.

13:51.997 --> 13:53.706
[sighs]

13:53.707 --> 13:55.292
I'm just glad you're safe.

13:56.752 --> 13:59.838
[grunts]
But no more dating

13:59.839 --> 14:02.257
older guys, ever,
you understand?

14:02.258 --> 14:04.509
The heart wants
what the heart wants, Dad.

14:04.510 --> 14:06.511
- Mm.
- But I'll do my best.

14:06.512 --> 14:08.137
[Dexter]
<i>My sister was always</i>

14:08.138 --> 14:09.973
<i>the most honest person
in the family.</i>

14:09.974 --> 14:12.559
I do have to give you some
bad news about your godfather.

14:12.560 --> 14:13.643
- Bobby?
- Yeah.

14:13.644 --> 14:15.228
He's been shot, he's in the ICU,

14:15.229 --> 14:16.813
and he's gonna be there
for a while.

14:16.814 --> 14:18.982
- Can I see him?
- No, they've restricted visitors

14:18.983 --> 14:20.650
- until his condition improves.
- Jesus Christ,

14:20.651 --> 14:22.277
there's got to be something
I can do.

14:22.278 --> 14:24.070
M-Miami Metro's having
a blood drive.

14:24.071 --> 14:25.572
Done. Where do I sign up?

14:25.573 --> 14:27.907
Why don't you bring
your sister to work?

14:27.908 --> 14:30.660
[crunching]

14:30.661 --> 14:33.204
<i>♪ mysterious, percussive music ♪</i>

14:33.205 --> 14:35.249
<i>♪</i>

14:43.132 --> 14:45.258
Been three days.

14:45.259 --> 14:47.719
People are probably starting
to feel like it's a lost cause.

14:47.720 --> 14:48.970
Well, fuck that.

14:48.971 --> 14:51.139
Hey, I got something!

14:51.140 --> 14:52.765
Over here.

14:52.766 --> 14:53.851
All right.

14:55.561 --> 14:57.437
[Brian]
Chinny-chin-chin.

14:57.438 --> 14:58.938
Hey!

14:58.939 --> 15:00.232
- [officer] Uh, yeah.
- [Harry] All right.

15:03.569 --> 15:04.569
[gasping]

15:04.570 --> 15:06.487
<i>♪ jarring music ♪</i>

15:06.488 --> 15:08.407
<i>♪</i>

15:10.701 --> 15:12.035
They killed 'em all.

15:12.036 --> 15:13.370
Oh, my...

15:14.496 --> 15:15.455
[Brian]
Help.

15:15.456 --> 15:18.082
Hey. Hey.

15:18.083 --> 15:19.626
Hey. Oh, God.

15:19.627 --> 15:21.044
Okay, I got you.

15:21.045 --> 15:22.588
- I got you.
- [grunts]

15:25.925 --> 15:27.301
All right.

15:37.603 --> 15:39.605
<i>♪</i>

15:55.579 --> 15:56.789
[slot opens]

15:59.875 --> 16:00.875
Dad!

16:00.876 --> 16:03.962
Dad, Dad, I know it's you.

16:03.963 --> 16:05.046
Please let me out of here.

16:05.047 --> 16:06.589
What did I do?

16:06.590 --> 16:08.383
Why did you do this?

16:08.384 --> 16:10.927
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

16:10.928 --> 16:13.263
You didn't do anything wrong.

16:14.264 --> 16:16.141
This will all be over soon.

16:17.142 --> 16:20.186
No, Dad, don't go, please!

16:20.187 --> 16:22.188
<i>♪ tense music ♪</i>

16:22.189 --> 16:24.524
<i>♪</i>

16:24.525 --> 16:25.942
[elevator bell dings]

16:25.943 --> 16:27.903
[indistinct chatter]

16:28.946 --> 16:31.490
Everyone loves Bobby, huh?

16:34.201 --> 16:35.368
[Dexter]
You can sign in over here.

16:35.369 --> 16:37.870
<i>♪ ethereal music ♪</i>

16:37.871 --> 16:39.872
<i>♪</i>

16:39.873 --> 16:42.041
Uh, I'll be around
if you need anything.

16:42.042 --> 16:43.167
You're not gonna wait with me?

16:43.168 --> 16:45.712
Got work to do, deadlines,

16:45.713 --> 16:47.213
but I'll give later.

16:47.214 --> 16:49.425
[man]
Kramer, Johnson. You're next.

16:51.552 --> 16:52.969
[Dexter] <i>Jimmy was killed
with an ice pick</i>

16:52.970 --> 16:54.179
<i>to the back of his head.</i>

16:55.180 --> 16:57.724
<i>The back of his shirt
was covered in blood.</i>

16:57.725 --> 17:00.728
<i>Nicky was alive
when this jersey was removed.</i>

17:09.528 --> 17:12.488
<i>♪ dramatic music ♪</i>

17:12.489 --> 17:13.781
Holy shit.

17:13.782 --> 17:16.868
This line is bananas.

17:16.869 --> 17:18.911
Morgan, you went
to medical school, right?

17:18.912 --> 17:20.121
Uh, nope, premed.

17:20.122 --> 17:21.205
Great. Want to draw blood,

17:21.206 --> 17:22.248
get that line moving?

17:22.249 --> 17:23.750
Uh, no, thanks.

17:23.751 --> 17:25.668
That wasn't an ask,
that was an order,

17:25.669 --> 17:28.087
but phrased nicely.

17:28.088 --> 17:29.922
Go forth, draw much blood.

17:29.923 --> 17:31.674
[Dexter]
<i>Any other time,</i>

17:31.675 --> 17:33.719
<i>that would have been
an exciting endeavor.</i>

17:34.678 --> 17:36.012
[Maria]
Is this records?

17:36.013 --> 17:37.555
Guilty as charged.

17:37.556 --> 17:40.016
I'm looking for a file from '73.

17:40.017 --> 17:42.435
Uh, the Estrada Cartel case.

17:42.436 --> 17:45.064
Started off at vice,
became a homicide.

17:48.442 --> 17:49.942
Camilla Figg.

17:49.943 --> 17:51.277
Guardian of Records
since time immemorial.

17:51.278 --> 17:52.278
And you are?

17:52.279 --> 17:54.238
Detective Maria LaGuerta.

17:54.239 --> 17:57.116
The new girl. We can always use
more estrogen in homicide.

17:57.117 --> 17:59.244
Welcome. Right this way.

18:02.956 --> 18:05.541
Here you go. Everything
you need to know and more.

18:05.542 --> 18:07.376
Real vicious bunch.

18:07.377 --> 18:08.587
[Maria]
Yeah.

18:12.091 --> 18:15.426
Oh, sorry, but do you mind?

18:15.427 --> 18:16.969
Of course.

18:16.970 --> 18:18.472
And don't bother refiling.
I'll handle it.

18:22.559 --> 18:23.976
[sighs softly]

18:23.977 --> 18:25.728
[humming]

18:25.729 --> 18:28.064
<i>♪ tense, dark music ♪</i>

18:28.065 --> 18:29.565
<i>♪</i>

18:29.566 --> 18:32.820
"One son, Brian Moser,
age seven."

18:34.404 --> 18:35.948
[scoffs]

18:37.324 --> 18:38.991
Got what I needed. Thanks.

18:38.992 --> 18:40.953
[Camilla]
We aim to please.

18:46.708 --> 18:48.251
[Harry]
All right...

18:48.252 --> 18:50.295
[phone ringing]

18:51.839 --> 18:54.173
[Camilla over phone]
<i>You were right. She came down.</i>

18:54.174 --> 18:55.800
She seem satisfied?

18:55.801 --> 18:58.177
There's no mention of Dexter
in any records.

18:58.178 --> 18:59.846
<i>LaGuerta's off the trail.</i>

18:59.847 --> 19:03.224
Great. Uh, any sign
of what I was looking for?

19:03.225 --> 19:04.225
Brian's youth records
are sealed.

19:04.226 --> 19:05.852
<i>Doubly so</i>

19:05.853 --> 19:07.228
<i>when there's medical records
attached.</i>

19:07.229 --> 19:09.313
- Any forwarding address?
<i>- Nothing.</i>

19:09.314 --> 19:11.065
No arrests.

19:11.066 --> 19:12.608
As far as I can tell,
Brian went to the Tampa facility

19:12.609 --> 19:15.278
<i>shortly after leaving you.</i>

19:15.279 --> 19:18.281
Harry. You all right?

19:18.282 --> 19:20.325
I'm good enough.

19:21.285 --> 19:23.036
[sighs]

19:31.962 --> 19:33.963
[sighs]

19:33.964 --> 19:36.008
<i>♪</i>

19:38.552 --> 19:40.595
- [fussing]
- [Barb] The state would prefer

19:40.596 --> 19:42.722
not to separate siblings.

19:42.723 --> 19:45.558
Is there any way you could
foster them as a pair?

19:45.559 --> 19:48.394
Uh, Brian has been
remarkably resilient

19:48.395 --> 19:50.521
considering what
they've been through.

19:50.522 --> 19:52.315
And Dexter,

19:52.316 --> 19:54.901
he hasn't said a word since,

19:54.902 --> 19:56.861
- well...
- [Doris] How did the boys

19:56.862 --> 19:58.697
come into state custody?

20:00.699 --> 20:03.702
Uh, their mother was, uh...

20:05.579 --> 20:08.164
...part of an undercover
drug case that went south.

20:08.165 --> 20:09.957
<i>♪ slow, dramatic music ♪</i>

20:09.958 --> 20:11.667
She was an informant

20:11.668 --> 20:13.086
and, uh...

20:14.755 --> 20:16.590
...murdered by the cartel.

20:18.133 --> 20:19.425
What about their father?

20:19.426 --> 20:21.093
He's in prison.

20:21.094 --> 20:23.554
Relinquished
all parental rights.

20:23.555 --> 20:25.806
Has zero interest
in being their father.

20:25.807 --> 20:27.266
So, they're on their own?

20:27.267 --> 20:28.435
Yeah.

20:32.731 --> 20:34.607
I need a moment with my husband.

20:34.608 --> 20:37.527
Oh, yeah. Sure.

20:44.117 --> 20:46.161
I just have one question.

20:47.788 --> 20:52.209
Is their mother Laura Moser?

20:53.669 --> 20:55.921
That woman
you had an affair with?

20:57.172 --> 20:59.258
[soft gasp]

21:02.135 --> 21:03.428
Yes.

21:16.191 --> 21:17.442
Hi.

21:19.319 --> 21:21.446
Do you like firetrucks?

21:32.541 --> 21:34.793
These boys need a mother.

21:44.678 --> 21:45.929
[fusses]

22:04.197 --> 22:06.866
[indistinct radio chatter]

22:06.867 --> 22:08.243
Hello.

22:10.078 --> 22:12.788
Um... Hi. Who are you?

22:12.789 --> 22:14.874
Oh. Sorry.
Yeah. I'm Debra Morgan.

22:14.875 --> 22:16.667
Deb. Harry's daughter.

22:16.668 --> 22:18.836
Maria. I work with your father.

22:18.837 --> 22:20.296
What you working on?

22:20.297 --> 22:22.048
Trying to catch
a possible serial killer.

22:22.049 --> 22:24.383
Like <i>Silence of the Lambs?</i>
Can I see?

22:24.384 --> 22:26.510
I'm sorry, but... no.

22:26.511 --> 22:27.970
Uh, where's your father?

22:27.971 --> 22:29.764
Hey.

22:29.765 --> 22:31.223
You're the other
Morgan kid, right?

22:31.224 --> 22:35.227
Yeah. Deb. You're Tanya?
My brother's boss?

22:35.228 --> 22:37.021
- The one and only.
- [chuckles softly]

22:37.022 --> 22:40.649
I love the idea of him being
ordered around by a lady boss.

22:40.650 --> 22:42.778
Well, I'm certainly
good at that.

22:49.117 --> 22:50.701
Did you always want to do this?

22:50.702 --> 22:52.745
Good question. No.

22:52.746 --> 22:56.248
When I was your age,
I was all about basketball.

22:56.249 --> 22:58.459
That's kind of tough
when you're fun-sized.

22:58.460 --> 22:59.752
And don't have a dick.

22:59.753 --> 23:01.087
[scoffs]
Tell me about it.

23:01.088 --> 23:02.088
Volleyball.

23:02.089 --> 23:03.756
You get it.

23:03.757 --> 23:05.716
Those little moments
where everything works out.

23:05.717 --> 23:08.511
You make a perfect pass
to your forward. They score.

23:08.512 --> 23:09.887
An impossible rebound.

23:09.888 --> 23:11.180
A diving bump
that saves the game.

23:11.181 --> 23:13.557
Fucking-A. Love those times.

23:13.558 --> 23:16.435
Endorphins flood your system.

23:16.436 --> 23:18.270
Singular moments.

23:18.271 --> 23:20.231
It's where happiness happens.

23:20.232 --> 23:22.233
So here,
it's catching criminals.

23:22.234 --> 23:24.568
Solving a mystery that
no one else can figure out?

23:24.569 --> 23:26.071
That's the shit.

23:27.906 --> 23:29.240
You got some blue in your blood?

23:29.241 --> 23:31.075
Considering the family business?

23:31.076 --> 23:33.285
Nah. That's a male Morgan thing.

23:33.286 --> 23:36.122
Hmm. That's too bad.

23:36.123 --> 23:38.708
We could always use
more kickass women around here.

23:41.086 --> 23:42.963
Come back and visit me anytime.

23:44.589 --> 23:46.590
<i>♪ gentle, hypnotic music ♪</i>

23:46.591 --> 23:48.635
<i>♪</i>

23:56.852 --> 23:59.019
<i>♪ soaring, intriguing music ♪</i>

23:59.020 --> 24:01.148
<i>♪</i>

24:14.327 --> 24:15.911
[Dexter]
<i>This was not the blood drive</i>

24:15.912 --> 24:17.079
<i>I was hoping for.</i>

24:17.080 --> 24:18.998
<i>Getting Spencer on my table</i>

24:18.999 --> 24:21.000
<i>was going to have to wait.</i>

24:21.001 --> 24:22.334
[sighs]

24:22.335 --> 24:23.502
<i>Or maybe not.</i>

24:23.503 --> 24:24.587
Captain!

24:24.588 --> 24:25.754
I see they've got you doing

24:25.755 --> 24:27.089
everything around here now.

24:27.090 --> 24:29.801
Yeah. Got a spot for you
right here.

24:34.014 --> 24:36.016
[groans]

24:38.393 --> 24:40.603
Now, you've done this
before, right?

24:40.604 --> 24:42.564
[chuckles softly]
Don't be nervous.

24:48.403 --> 24:50.613
- Steady.
- Mm-hmm.

24:50.614 --> 24:51.781
That's good.

24:57.370 --> 24:59.413
Here, let me move
that up for you.

24:59.414 --> 25:01.208
- Thanks.
- Mm-hmm.

25:06.296 --> 25:07.338
Nice veins.

25:07.339 --> 25:08.632
Hmm. [scoffs]

25:16.306 --> 25:17.516
[groans softly]

25:26.858 --> 25:30.069
I can't imagine the pain
you and your wife must be in.

25:30.070 --> 25:31.529
Ex-wife.

25:31.530 --> 25:35.033
Yeah. She's-she's just a wreck.

25:36.076 --> 25:37.576
[sighs]

25:37.577 --> 25:39.078
Did you find anything
at the Tigres house

25:39.079 --> 25:40.788
that could help me find my son?

25:40.789 --> 25:42.581
Want some good news?

25:42.582 --> 25:44.708
- Yeah.
- Blood on Nicky's jersey wasn't

25:44.709 --> 25:46.502
indicative of a fatal wound.

25:46.503 --> 25:48.170
It was only on the front.

25:48.171 --> 25:50.589
And most likely from the...
finger amputation.

25:50.590 --> 25:52.216
Yeah.

25:52.217 --> 25:54.760
[Dexter] <i>He was a better actor
than a cop.</i>

25:54.761 --> 25:56.595
So, he could still be alive?

25:56.596 --> 25:58.806
There's a solid chance he is.

25:58.807 --> 26:01.226
I'll take any hope I can get.

26:06.314 --> 26:08.900
Why do you think the cartel has
targeted children?

26:11.069 --> 26:13.071
They're fucking evil animals.

26:16.533 --> 26:18.492
[sighs]
I couldn't agree more.

26:18.493 --> 26:19.578
Yeah.

26:20.620 --> 26:22.246
People who hurt kids...

26:22.247 --> 26:23.415
Hmm.

26:24.541 --> 26:25.958
[hisses]

26:25.959 --> 26:28.420
[Dexter]
<i>Chalked that up to foreplay.</i>

26:33.091 --> 26:34.633
I hope you do a better job

26:34.634 --> 26:36.135
with the cold cases
I assigned you

26:36.136 --> 26:38.262
than you do drawing blood.

26:38.263 --> 26:41.766
Well, actually, hoping to turn
the corner on a big case.

26:42.726 --> 26:45.978
Tonight could even be the night.

26:45.979 --> 26:47.896
Good.

26:47.897 --> 26:50.650
We need some good news
around here.

26:53.528 --> 26:55.113
Oh. Your turn.

26:56.489 --> 26:59.825
Morgan. Consider
your blood drive days over.

26:59.826 --> 27:02.286
<i>♪ gentle, dramatic music ♪</i>

27:02.287 --> 27:05.457
[Dexter] <i>Every day we leave
evidence of ourselves behind.</i>

27:07.375 --> 27:08.627
<i>Whether we like it or not.</i>

27:10.503 --> 27:13.213
<i>DNA, hair,</i>

27:13.214 --> 27:14.758
<i>dandruff...</i>

27:16.176 --> 27:17.802
<i>Fingerprints.</i>

27:20.138 --> 27:24.266
<i>Identifiers of who we are.
Where we've been.</i>

27:24.267 --> 27:26.727
Hey, Dex. Can I ask a favor?

27:26.728 --> 27:28.688
What's up?

27:31.191 --> 27:34.693
I... want to donate blood.
For Bobby.

27:34.694 --> 27:36.862
Great.
The line's gone down a lot.

27:36.863 --> 27:39.448
The-the-the thing is...
I-I can't.

27:39.449 --> 27:41.492
I'm sure Bobby'll have
more than enough blood.

27:41.493 --> 27:43.077
That's the problem.

27:43.078 --> 27:45.204
Everyone is doing it.
Hell, even your sister.

27:45.205 --> 27:46.538
People ask questions.

27:46.539 --> 27:47.748
[Dexter]
<i>There were some mysteries</i>

27:47.749 --> 27:48.999
<i>even I couldn't fathom.</i>

27:49.000 --> 27:51.627
You know about me. Yeah?

27:51.628 --> 27:53.213
Yeah?

27:54.214 --> 27:57.216
Last month I, uh...

27:57.217 --> 27:59.134
I got a call
from a former partner

27:59.135 --> 28:00.679
who tested positive.

28:02.430 --> 28:03.722
For HIV?

28:03.723 --> 28:04.723
Oh.

28:04.724 --> 28:07.226
Yeah. I-I got tested,

28:07.227 --> 28:09.520
but it-it's still
a few weeks away from results.

28:09.521 --> 28:10.938
[Dexter]
<i>This is what happens</i>

28:10.939 --> 28:13.023
<i>to normal people
with big secrets.</i>

28:13.024 --> 28:16.402
<i>It's harder for them
to keep their masks on straight.</i>

28:16.403 --> 28:18.278
I've got you.

28:18.279 --> 28:20.280
<i>♪ gentle music ♪</i>

28:20.281 --> 28:22.367
<i>♪</i>

28:31.918 --> 28:34.378
<i>It was odd being
the blood giver...</i>

28:34.379 --> 28:36.672
<i>but as a budding master
at keeping secrets,</i>

28:36.673 --> 28:39.551
<i>it felt good to help a novice.</i>

28:44.723 --> 28:46.348
Thanks again.
You're a lifesaver.

28:46.349 --> 28:48.767
[Dexter] <i>I'd never been
called that before.</i>

28:48.768 --> 28:50.145
Have a cookie.

28:58.820 --> 29:00.946
[Dexter exhales]

29:00.947 --> 29:02.489
Somebody still hasn't
given blood.

29:02.490 --> 29:04.825
I have an intense fear
of needles.

29:04.826 --> 29:07.119
Specifically when they are
poked into me.

29:07.120 --> 29:08.662
You just haven't been poked
in the right place, my friend.

29:08.663 --> 29:11.373
- [chuckles]
- Yeah.

29:11.374 --> 29:14.585
Thanks anyway,
but I think I have to pass.

29:14.586 --> 29:16.670
I'd hate to faint
in front of the guys.

29:16.671 --> 29:18.172
Listen, intern.
One of our own is in need.

29:18.173 --> 29:19.173
This is what we do.

29:19.174 --> 29:20.550
Which arm?

29:21.718 --> 29:24.053
[groans softly]
Left, please.

29:29.726 --> 29:31.727
<i>♪ slow, somber music ♪</i>

29:31.728 --> 29:34.564
<i>♪</i>

29:45.116 --> 29:46.450
[sighs loudly]

29:46.451 --> 29:47.951
[Doris]
Can you smile for Mama?

29:47.952 --> 29:49.162
- Yes.
- [baby cooing]

29:50.163 --> 29:51.539
What?

29:53.500 --> 29:55.000
Dexie's hungry.

29:55.001 --> 29:56.418
He wants a peanut butter
and jelly sandwich.

29:56.419 --> 29:58.338
Okay.

30:00.507 --> 30:02.841
I'm just gonna put Debbie down.

30:02.842 --> 30:05.637
- [cooing]
- Okay.

30:08.556 --> 30:11.017
[Deb fussing]

30:11.976 --> 30:14.479
[Deb crying]

30:20.026 --> 30:21.985
Mommy will be right back.

30:21.986 --> 30:23.195
[Deb wailing]

30:23.196 --> 30:24.863
Shut up.

30:24.864 --> 30:26.532
<i>♪ dark, suspenseful music ♪</i>

30:26.533 --> 30:28.535
<i>♪</i>

30:38.253 --> 30:40.087
[muffled crying]

30:40.088 --> 30:41.506
[grunting]

30:44.300 --> 30:46.803
What are you doing?

30:47.929 --> 30:50.097
[Deb wailing]

30:50.098 --> 30:51.641
[shushing]

30:52.642 --> 30:54.560
Why did you do that?

30:54.561 --> 30:55.854
Too noisy.

30:56.938 --> 30:58.981
Brian, you are in a time-out.

30:58.982 --> 31:01.692
Just stay on the couch
until Harry comes home.

31:01.693 --> 31:03.695
<i>♪</i>

31:17.876 --> 31:19.544
[sighs]

31:22.714 --> 31:26.258
Hey, we got to talk
about what you did to Deb.

31:26.259 --> 31:29.094
That was really dangerous,
and you could've hurt her.

31:29.095 --> 31:30.470
<i>♪ dark, eerie music ♪</i>

31:30.471 --> 31:32.556
Don't just shrug.

31:32.557 --> 31:34.141
You can't do things like that.

31:34.142 --> 31:36.226
You're not my dad.

31:36.227 --> 31:38.437
[scoffs] Uh, I know.

31:38.438 --> 31:40.272
I'm not.

31:40.273 --> 31:42.107
Doris and I, we're both here

31:42.108 --> 31:44.318
to take care of you
and your brother.

31:44.319 --> 31:47.070
I don't want you to.
I want to go home.

31:47.071 --> 31:48.614
I miss my mom!

31:48.615 --> 31:50.908
- [panting]
- Hey, hey.

31:50.909 --> 31:52.117
Look. Hey. Come on.
Take it easy.

31:52.118 --> 31:53.285
[grunting]

31:53.286 --> 31:54.995
- I hate this place!
- [grunts]

31:54.996 --> 31:57.414
This isn't our home!

31:57.415 --> 31:59.416
I hate you!

31:59.417 --> 32:01.669
I hate all of you!

32:03.338 --> 32:05.255
<i>♪ tense, dramatic music ♪</i>

32:05.256 --> 32:06.298
[Doris and Harry gasping]

32:06.299 --> 32:08.259
Leave me alone!

32:15.266 --> 32:16.434
Oh. [whimpers]

32:18.144 --> 32:20.312
I cross-checked
recently released patients

32:20.313 --> 32:22.272
from that Tampa hospital
against our records.

32:22.273 --> 32:23.732
- And?
- [stammers]

32:23.733 --> 32:25.359
Three have addresses
in Dade County,

32:25.360 --> 32:27.277
two have been arrested.

32:27.278 --> 32:30.155
- I'm gonna give them a visit.
- Hmm, nice work.

32:30.156 --> 32:31.657
Uh, if you don't mind,
I'm gonna go through our files,

32:31.658 --> 32:33.367
see if there's anything
I've missed.

32:33.368 --> 32:34.618
- Do your thing.
- Mm-hmm.

32:34.619 --> 32:36.537
- Keep me posted.
- Will do.

32:38.831 --> 32:40.582
[sighs] All right.

32:40.583 --> 32:41.959
<i>♪ dark, atmospheric music ♪</i>

32:41.960 --> 32:43.835
Raul...

32:43.836 --> 32:45.545
<i>♪</i>

32:45.546 --> 32:47.590
[exhales]
...what did you do to Brian?

32:55.515 --> 32:56.682
[sighs]

32:56.683 --> 32:58.183
All right.

32:58.184 --> 33:00.853
He's an orphan.
Foster care like Brian.

33:07.068 --> 33:08.695
[exhales]

33:19.372 --> 33:21.707
[sighs]

33:21.708 --> 33:23.334
[scoffs]

33:29.090 --> 33:31.676
Holy shit.

33:33.011 --> 33:35.262
<i>♪ tense, suspenseful music ♪</i>

33:35.263 --> 33:36.931
<i>♪</i>

33:41.269 --> 33:43.062
Fucker is stalking my son.

33:44.105 --> 33:45.982
[gasps]
Oh, my God.

33:46.983 --> 33:49.192
This seven-card approach
is a game changer.

33:49.193 --> 33:50.861
I'm only one call away
on three of them.

33:50.862 --> 33:54.114
All I need is I-24,
and that sweet

33:54.115 --> 33:57.076
- $75 jackpot is mine.
- [balls clattering]

33:58.411 --> 34:01.079
Uh, I-25.

34:01.080 --> 34:03.041
I-25.

34:06.127 --> 34:07.335
[Brian]
Bingo.

34:07.336 --> 34:09.087
[scoffs]
About time you won.

34:09.088 --> 34:11.257
Hey. Let's celebrate.

34:12.216 --> 34:14.551
Applebee's, on me?

34:14.552 --> 34:18.473
Dinner with you would make
a nice consolation prize.

34:20.058 --> 34:21.476
[chuckles]

34:24.103 --> 34:26.063
I think I might be
addicted to bingo.

34:26.064 --> 34:27.522
[chuckles]

34:27.523 --> 34:29.066
You think there's
a Bingo's Anonymous,

34:29.067 --> 34:30.275
in case my addiction
gets out of hand?

34:30.276 --> 34:32.569
[laughs]
Yeah.

34:32.570 --> 34:35.655
[clears throat]
Is-is that your car?

34:35.656 --> 34:37.449
[Brian]
Your chariot awaits.

34:37.450 --> 34:38.743
[Barb chuckles]

34:41.329 --> 34:42.621
Um...

34:42.622 --> 34:44.289
I can't sit back there.

34:44.290 --> 34:45.458
I want to sit up front.

34:46.459 --> 34:49.127
Well, Barb...

34:49.128 --> 34:52.131
life is full of wants
and desires.

34:53.341 --> 34:54.633
I wanted to spend my life

34:54.634 --> 34:57.762
with my little brother...
Dexter.

35:01.641 --> 35:02.975
B-Brian?

35:04.227 --> 35:05.811
Brian Moser?

35:05.812 --> 35:07.646
[both grunt]

35:07.647 --> 35:10.483
<i>♪ dark, tense music ♪</i>

35:18.950 --> 35:20.952
[unlocks door]

35:23.121 --> 35:25.122
Hello?

35:25.123 --> 35:27.792
Dad? Dexter?

35:30.002 --> 35:31.462
[sighs]

35:32.380 --> 35:33.922
[answering machine beeps]

35:33.923 --> 35:35.507
[woman over machine]
<i>Hi, Debra Morgan.</i>

35:35.508 --> 35:38.093
<i>It's Kelsey from
Florida State University.</i>

35:38.094 --> 35:40.011
<i>We've been made aware
of the incident</i>

35:40.012 --> 35:41.847
<i>at your high school last week,</i>

35:41.848 --> 35:43.682
<i>but the coach
rewatched your tape</i>

35:43.683 --> 35:46.852
<i>and is still interested
in meeting about a scholarship.</i>

35:46.853 --> 35:48.353
<i>If you wouldn't mind
calling us back</i>

35:48.354 --> 35:50.021
<i>at the FSU
administrative office,</i>

35:50.022 --> 35:51.189
<i>we'd love to hear
from you. Thanks.</i>

35:51.190 --> 35:52.524
[machine beeps]

35:52.525 --> 35:54.526
<i>♪ suspenseful music ♪</i>

35:54.527 --> 35:56.612
<i>♪</i>

36:02.577 --> 36:04.620
[video games blipping]

36:12.753 --> 36:15.297
[Dexter]
<i>I'd been feeling...</i>

36:15.298 --> 36:17.174
<i>unsettled</i>

36:17.175 --> 36:20.552
<i>ever since I'd seen Jimmy
hanging from that bridge.</i>

36:20.553 --> 36:23.054
<i>But I never dreamed
that it would be my blade</i>

36:23.055 --> 36:25.390
<i>that ended
Jimmy's killer's life.</i>

36:25.391 --> 36:27.809
<i>Spencer was exactly
the sort of person</i>

36:27.810 --> 36:30.645
<i>Harry created the Code for.</i>

36:30.646 --> 36:31.689
[grunts]

36:32.732 --> 36:34.900
[inhales sharply, sighs]

36:34.901 --> 36:36.903
<i>Too bad Harry
didn't see it that way...</i>

36:38.529 --> 36:39.614
<i>...yet.</i>

36:42.366 --> 36:45.118
<i>Note to self: giving blood
is harder than taking it.</i>

36:45.119 --> 36:46.370
Mmm.

37:01.552 --> 37:03.054
[door closes]

37:06.140 --> 37:09.434
"$5,000 cash" by 1 a.m.

37:09.435 --> 37:11.603
"or I tell the world."

37:11.604 --> 37:14.190
[groans]
Fucking Victor.

37:26.619 --> 37:28.078
[monitor beeping steadily]

37:28.079 --> 37:29.913
Come in.

37:29.914 --> 37:32.290
[exhales, sniffles]

37:32.291 --> 37:33.792
[Harry sighs]

37:33.793 --> 37:35.461
[Missy] Thank you
for taking the late shift.

37:38.422 --> 37:41.091
Are you kidding? I'd do anything
for this big tub of love.

37:41.092 --> 37:43.135
[sniffles]

37:45.471 --> 37:46.681
[kisses]

37:48.266 --> 37:50.642
Don't be kissing my husband
while he's unconscious.

37:50.643 --> 37:52.644
[laughs softly]
While he's unconscious.

37:52.645 --> 37:54.772
- [laughs softly]
- Okay, I got it.

38:02.530 --> 38:04.448
[exhales]

38:05.866 --> 38:08.618
I'm...

38:08.619 --> 38:09.869
[sighs]

38:09.870 --> 38:11.789
I'm sorry I wasn't there
for you.

38:15.042 --> 38:17.836
[sighs]

38:17.837 --> 38:21.465
So much I want to tell you,
ask you.

38:23.175 --> 38:26.136
Mm. For the first time,
you can't complain

38:26.137 --> 38:28.180
that I'm yapping too much.

38:29.807 --> 38:33.144
You know those murders LaGuerta
and I have been saddled with?

38:35.187 --> 38:38.857
Turns out, you and I know
who the perp is.

38:38.858 --> 38:41.319
Brian Moser.

38:42.361 --> 38:44.030
Dexter's brother.

38:45.865 --> 38:48.326
I haven't told LaGuerta.

38:51.037 --> 38:53.371
This is the point
where I need to use

38:53.372 --> 38:55.957
that big brain of yours.

38:55.958 --> 38:58.793
[sighs]

38:58.794 --> 39:01.379
Brian wants to connect
with Dexter

39:01.380 --> 39:03.341
for whatever fucked-up reason.

39:05.509 --> 39:10.348
And if I bring Brian in,
he blows up everything.

39:14.268 --> 39:17.897
Dexter will learn
the gory details...

39:18.898 --> 39:21.233
...of his god-awful past.

39:22.985 --> 39:24.486
[sighs]

39:24.487 --> 39:26.364
Who knows
what that'll do to him?

39:31.369 --> 39:34.162
What do I do, Bobby?

39:34.163 --> 39:35.873
[sighs]

39:43.172 --> 39:45.173
[whispers]
Hey.

39:45.174 --> 39:46.425
What?

39:47.385 --> 39:49.052
What?

39:49.053 --> 39:50.429
Save...

39:51.472 --> 39:53.224
...Dexter.

39:54.725 --> 39:56.226
[chuckles]
Hey!

39:56.227 --> 39:58.646
Hey, Doc! He's awake!

40:00.147 --> 40:03.775
[Doris]
He's had flashes of violence.

40:03.776 --> 40:05.403
He put our baby in danger.

40:06.904 --> 40:08.738
So I'm-I'm afraid
we can't handle his...

40:08.739 --> 40:10.950
level of trauma.

40:11.992 --> 40:13.494
What about Dexter?

40:15.496 --> 40:17.997
We've grown to really love him.

40:17.998 --> 40:20.625
[Harry]
We know that the state

40:20.626 --> 40:23.712
doesn't want to split siblings,
but... [sighs]

40:26.966 --> 40:29.634
<i>♪ somber music ♪</i>

40:29.635 --> 40:31.679
<i>♪</i>

40:33.514 --> 40:36.225
Daddy, where's Biney going?

40:37.184 --> 40:38.894
[baby Deb cooing]

40:44.608 --> 40:46.569
- [car door closes]
- [engine starts]

41:15.222 --> 41:17.599
<i>♪ pulsing music ♪</i>

41:17.600 --> 41:19.727
<i>♪</i>

41:47.546 --> 41:48.630
[video games blipping]

41:48.631 --> 41:50.216
What the fuck?

41:53.469 --> 41:56.055
[both grunting]

42:01.769 --> 42:02.853
[straining]

42:16.575 --> 42:18.118
[panting]

42:21.580 --> 42:23.540
[grunts]

42:23.541 --> 42:26.084
[Dexter] <i>I learned
a valuable lesson that night.</i>

42:26.085 --> 42:29.128
<i>Never give two pints of blood
on stalk-and-kill days.</i>

42:29.129 --> 42:30.798
[panting]

42:35.928 --> 42:37.012
[Spencer grunting]

42:39.640 --> 42:41.599
<i>[video game music playing]</i>

42:41.600 --> 42:43.644
<i>♪</i>

42:45.813 --> 42:46.980
Dexter?

42:46.981 --> 42:49.857
[video game characters grunting]

42:49.858 --> 42:51.151
What is this?

42:52.611 --> 42:54.613
Trying to beat one
of Nicky's top scores.

42:56.824 --> 42:59.867
- [buzzer sounds]
- [groans]

42:59.868 --> 43:02.621
I'm gonna put in
your boy's initials.

43:04.665 --> 43:06.584
Least I can do for him.

43:10.546 --> 43:13.381
What the hell is going on?

43:13.382 --> 43:15.133
Oh, let's not play that game.

43:15.134 --> 43:18.637
I think we both know
what's going on here.

43:20.222 --> 43:23.933
Why do you have those pictures
up there? Why my son?

43:23.934 --> 43:26.854
[laughs]
Wow.

43:28.147 --> 43:31.149
You are one great actor.

43:31.150 --> 43:33.318
How do you do that?

43:33.319 --> 43:36.654
How do you, who is,
as you yourself said,

43:36.655 --> 43:38.281
"a fucking evil animal,"

43:38.282 --> 43:42.119
give such a convincing,
innocent performance?

43:43.120 --> 43:44.412
You have the wrong guy.

43:44.413 --> 43:46.915
Oh, no, you're the right guy.

43:49.001 --> 43:52.003
Remember that blood on the box
that held your son's finger?

43:52.004 --> 43:54.005
Your first mistake.

43:54.006 --> 43:56.174
I could've passed it off
as a coincidence,

43:56.175 --> 43:57.383
but that wound
on your forearm...

43:57.384 --> 43:58.551
[groans]

43:58.552 --> 44:00.596
Nicky fought back, didn't he?

44:02.139 --> 44:04.642
He's older than Jimmy,
tougher to wrangle.

44:07.186 --> 44:09.145
And then there was
that hesitation mark

44:09.146 --> 44:11.272
on Nicky's finger.

44:11.273 --> 44:16.194
Was it hard, even for "a fucking
evil animal" like you,

44:16.195 --> 44:19.156
to cut off
your own son's finger?

44:20.491 --> 44:24.786
But the real proof?
Undeniable?

44:24.787 --> 44:28.499
When I saw you give your son's
bloody jersey to that junkie.

44:30.376 --> 44:33.837
Then you killed those Los Tigres
members to cover it up.

44:37.174 --> 44:39.677
And let's not forget
what happened to Bobby.

44:42.680 --> 44:44.389
[whispers]
I like him.

44:44.390 --> 44:46.933
I like him, too.

44:46.934 --> 44:50.187
How many other children have
you murdered over the years?

44:51.897 --> 44:53.064
None.

44:53.065 --> 44:56.609
[groans softly]
Seriously?

44:56.610 --> 44:57.944
Drop the innocent act.

44:57.945 --> 44:59.529
- [gasps]
- How many?

44:59.530 --> 45:02.741
I am not a serial killer.

45:04.076 --> 45:06.160
I protected this city.

45:06.161 --> 45:09.831
I spent my entire life
in the pursuit of justice.

45:09.832 --> 45:12.250
I'm a goddamn hero!

45:12.251 --> 45:15.169
I thought you were a hero.

45:15.170 --> 45:17.922
You were always one
of the good guys to me.

45:17.923 --> 45:20.591
I am one of the good guys.

45:20.592 --> 45:23.386
Good guys don't kill kids.

45:23.387 --> 45:25.722
She betrayed me.

45:25.723 --> 45:27.306
Becca?

45:27.307 --> 45:32.019
Betrayed my family
and turned Nicky against me.

45:32.020 --> 45:36.691
Oh, you did all this to...
to hurt your ex-wife?

45:36.692 --> 45:39.193
Aren't you a fucking genius?

45:39.194 --> 45:41.571
[Dexter] <i>In that moment
I realized a single incident</i>

45:41.572 --> 45:44.907
<i>could turn a good person
into a monster.</i>

45:44.908 --> 45:47.076
<i>It was a sobering realization.</i>

45:47.077 --> 45:49.662
<i>The world became
an even darker place.</i>

45:49.663 --> 45:51.581
Let me go.

45:51.582 --> 45:53.375
I'll tell you where Nicky is.

45:54.334 --> 45:58.922
You kill me,
he'll die of starvation.

45:59.923 --> 46:00.966
Tell me.

46:01.967 --> 46:05.804
You heard me. There's only
one way to find out.

46:10.642 --> 46:12.852
[Spencer grunts]

46:12.853 --> 46:14.729
Fuck.

46:14.730 --> 46:16.147
- [strains]
- Want to feel

46:16.148 --> 46:18.399
- how Nicky and Jimmy felt?
- [strains]

46:18.400 --> 46:21.319
I guarantee zero
hesitation marks when I do it.

46:21.320 --> 46:22.487
Fuck you!

46:22.488 --> 46:25.406
[screams]

46:25.407 --> 46:26.824
[grunts]

46:26.825 --> 46:28.785
Did your son scream like that?

46:28.786 --> 46:30.244
[grunts]

46:30.245 --> 46:31.788
Did Jimmy Powell?

46:31.789 --> 46:33.457
[pants]

46:34.082 --> 46:35.958
- [both grunt]
- [Dexter] <i>That moment</i>

46:35.959 --> 46:39.086
<i>was the worst case of serial
killer blue balls I'd ever had.</i>

46:39.087 --> 46:41.506
I've learned firsthand
you can lose two pints of blood

46:41.507 --> 46:43.800
and still function,
but when you get to three,

46:43.801 --> 46:47.762
it's a little iffy,
mortally speaking.

46:47.763 --> 46:50.724
Let me go.

46:53.519 --> 46:57.647
No. I'm gonna let you sit here
and think about what you did.

46:57.648 --> 46:59.482
[panting]

46:59.483 --> 47:02.401
And when I get back...

47:02.402 --> 47:04.987
you better be more forthcoming
about Nicky.

47:04.988 --> 47:06.949
[Spencer panting]

47:20.087 --> 47:21.295
- [exhales]
- [door closes]

47:21.296 --> 47:23.882
[grunting, panting]

47:29.721 --> 47:31.013
[grunts]

47:31.014 --> 47:33.016
[panting]

47:38.397 --> 47:40.898
<i>♪ urgent music ♪</i>

47:40.899 --> 47:43.026
<i>♪</i>

47:43.944 --> 47:46.070
[sniffles]

47:46.071 --> 47:47.447
[groans]

47:48.407 --> 47:50.908
[shudders]

47:50.909 --> 47:54.328
What are you,
what are you doing?

47:54.329 --> 47:56.873
You remember
what you promised me?

47:56.874 --> 47:59.793
[exhales sharply]
I'm sor...

48:01.461 --> 48:03.212
I'm sorry.

48:03.213 --> 48:04.715
You, uh...

48:06.508 --> 48:08.175
...you needed help.

48:08.176 --> 48:09.802
What I needed was my family.

48:09.803 --> 48:11.221
[exhales sharply]

48:12.514 --> 48:13.890
My brother.

48:13.891 --> 48:15.683
[whimpers]

48:15.684 --> 48:17.977
I, I, uh...

48:17.978 --> 48:20.313
I did what I thought was best

48:20.314 --> 48:23.190
for you and your brother, Brian.

48:23.191 --> 48:24.401
[gasps]

48:25.944 --> 48:30.865
[crying]
No. No.

48:30.866 --> 48:32.326
[sobs]

48:34.411 --> 48:37.622
No. Please.

48:37.623 --> 48:39.415
[sobs]

48:39.416 --> 48:41.792
You promised me,

48:41.793 --> 48:45.296
you wouldn't separate
me and Dexter.

48:45.297 --> 48:46.964
I'm sorry. I'm sorry.

48:46.965 --> 48:48.675
But you did.

48:50.636 --> 48:53.513
So... now...

48:55.182 --> 48:56.265
- [chain saw starts]
- No!

48:56.266 --> 48:59.810
[crying]
No...

48:59.811 --> 49:01.646
...I'm gonna separate you.

49:01.647 --> 49:05.274
Help me! Help me!
[whimpers]

49:05.275 --> 49:06.985
[chain saw revving]

49:08.820 --> 49:10.280
[whimpering]

49:15.243 --> 49:17.536
[panting]

49:17.537 --> 49:19.623
[grunting]

49:23.126 --> 49:24.710
[engine starts]

49:24.711 --> 49:26.797
[tires screeching]

49:34.513 --> 49:36.806
[Dexter] <i>Tamping down
my Dark Passenger's urges</i>

49:36.807 --> 49:38.349
<i>was never easy,</i>

49:38.350 --> 49:40.685
<i>but when a child's life
was at stake,</i>

49:40.686 --> 49:43.145
<i>it felt... right.</i>

49:43.146 --> 49:44.690
[tires screeching]

49:50.988 --> 49:53.489
<i>♪ atmospheric music ♪</i>

49:53.490 --> 49:58.495
<i>♪</i>
